snippet.title: Comcast 1Q earns surge on upbeat NBC results
snippet.description: Comcast Corp. said Tuesday that its first-quarter net income rose by 30 percent as ad revenue surged at broadcast network NBC, helped by the Winter Olympics in Sochi and Jimmy Fallon's elevation as host of "The Tonight Show."

snippet.title: Correction: Illinois Medicaid-Overpayments story
snippet.description: In a story April 18 about Illinois Medicaid paying an estimated $12 million for services for people listed in state records as deceased, The Associated Press erroneously reported that the state's contract with Maximus Health Services ended last year. The state continues to have a contract with Maximus for some services, but, effective May 1, state employees will work with the company to verify Medicaid eligibility.

snippet.title: Attacks on payment systems trail other cybercrimes
snippet.description: While the theft of millions of credit card numbers from Target customers last year drew attention to Internet crime, a new study finds that breaches of retail payment systems are less common than other kinds of attacks.

snippet.title: After three-year slump, lobbying industry shows signs of growth
snippet.description: The District's 10 largest lobby shops by revenue reported a collective 3 percent increase in lobbying fees during the first quarter of 2014 compared to the first quarter of 2013. But the growth is unevenly spread, and is a far cry from the industry's peak years of 2009 and 2010.

snippet.title: Kansas farmer gets kidney donation from hunter
snippet.description: Two hunters brought together by a love of the outdoors formed a friendship leading one to donate a kidney to the other, a friendship that has led to a foundation aimed at sharing the outdoors with others.

snippet.title: 1 year after bombs, Boston Marathon a celebration
snippet.description: Unfinished business. Defiance. Hope, strength and resilience. They used different words but the meaning was the same for thousands of people who were stopped by twin bombings at last year's Boston Marathon and came back this year to finish what they started.

Myanmar rebel leader urges US role in peace talks
snippet.description: A leader of ethnic Kachin rebels battling government forces in Myanmar has urged the U.S. to play a role in peace talks to quell decades of conflict in the country's lawless border regions.
